* Get started buying bitcoins at [[Coinbase|Coinbase_(business)]], [[Bitstamp]] or [[Cubits]].
* Start by watching [this 2 minute introduction video](http://weusecoins.com/).
* Learn why it [could be a good investment](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/2834/what-are-the-perceived-advantages-of-bitcoin-as-a-store-of-value), or an objectively [better means of exchange](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/305/what-are-the-perceived-advantages-of-bitcoin-as-a-means-of-exchange).
* Get a [[client|Clients]] and try it out yourself.
* For 1 BTC or less, use an [[online wallet|Browser-based_wallet]] that you trust. 
* When storing large amounts of BTC, use [[paper wallets|paper_wallet]].
* Explore bitcoin history with a [[block chain browser|Block_chain_browser]].
* Ask a question at [StackExchange](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/) or [BitcoinTalk](http://bitcointalk.org).
* [Can I generate Free Money on my computer?](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/118/how-much-bitcoin-will-i-mine-right-now-with-hardware-x) (No, that's no longer possible.)
* Browse the [[FAQ]].
* [[Where can I buy bitcoins?|Buying_Bitcoins_(the_noob_version)]] (Hint: [You can't buy them with Paypal or credit cards](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/2293/how-can-i-buy-bitcoin-via-a-credit-card-or-paypal))

If you're looking for how to get started with Bitcoin-Qt, [[this is the article you're looking for|Getting_started_installing_bitcoin-qt]].

